    "long_instructions": "### Alternating Patterns\r\n\r\n**Define:** DJs often play one track while preparing the next one, switching smoothly between songs during a performance. In this challenge, you'll use nested loops to switch between two musical sections, giving you time to experiment and make live edits.\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Plan two different musical sections. Each one should include a drum, bass, and lead part. Think about how they'll sound different from each other and how you want them to alternate. Decide how to layer each section using `play together`.\r\n\r\n**Try:**\r\n\r\n- Create your first loop to repeat 3 times with a drum, bass, and lead using `play together`.\r\n- Create your second loop the same way, using different tracks.\r\n- Nest both loops inside a larger loop that repeats 3 times.\r\n\r\nRun your code and experiment! While one loop plays, the other is silent so you can make live changes.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/d72b72550ef9788958d1e0a8449e8530-image-1745295546774.png)\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Did switching between the loops feel smooth? Were you able to edit or tweak one loop while the other played? In order to complete this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- Two different loops that each repeat 3 times\r\n- Each loop includes a drum, bass, and lead layered with `play together`\r\n- Both loops nested inside another loop that repeats at least 3 times",
    "exemplar_settings": {
      "playerEnabled": false,
      "validationEnabled": false
    },
    "display_name": "Alternating Tracks",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Use nested loops to alternate between two sets of beats, similar to how a DJ uses a turntable to play one record while they setup the next song.",
